

=Definition=

Boris Pluskowski:

Social team : "a collection of individuals who have a common understanding of the "game they are playing" (i.e. the team's purpose); know in which goal they are trying to score (i.e. have a shared understanding of what a "win" looks like); and are collaborating together to achieve that aim."
(http://completeinnovator.com/2010/02/09/defining-the-%E2%80%9Csocial-team%E2%80%9D/)


